==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Contract tablet
<hw>Con"tract tablet</hw>. <fld>(Babylonian & Assyrian Antiq.)</fld>
<def>A clay tablet on which was inscribed a contract, for safe keeping.
Such tablets were inclosed in an outer case (often called the
<it>envelope</it>), on which was inscribed a duplicate of the
inscription on the inclosed tablet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Contracture</ent>⟦br⟧
